1. Tylenol 650 mg p.o. q.6h. and p.r.n.
2. Azathioprine 50 mg p.o. daily.
3. Calcitrol 0.25 mcg p.o. daily.
4. Codeine 15-30 mg p.o. q.4h. p.r.n.
5. Neoral cyclosporin 50 mg p.o. b.i.d.
6. Colace 100 mg p.o. b.i.d.
7. Lasix 80 mg p.o. daily.
8. Amaryl 3 mg p.o. q.p.m.
9. Regular insulin sliding scale.
10. Potassium chloride slow release 10 mEq p.o. daily.
11. Labetalol 600 mg p.o. b.i.d.
12. Magnesium oxide 420 mg p.o. daily.
13. Rapamune 2 mg p.o. daily.
14. Sulfinpyrazone 200 mg p.o. b.i.d.
15. Timolol 0.5% one drop OU q.a.m.
FOLLOW-UP PLAN:
The patient is to keep the wound clean and dry until his follow
up. He is to follow up with Dr. Bouwens on 6/15/06 .  He is to
contact the office or the hospital if he has any worrisome
symptoms , worsening pain , fevers , etc.
